# Force LF line endings on shell-script-style files.
#
# Background: scripts/pre-commit-safety.mjs starts with a shebang line
# (#!/usr/bin/env node). On Windows clients with core.autocrlf=true the
# checkout converts to CRLF, producing `#!/usr/bin/env node\r\n` at the
# top of the file. Vitest's transform pipeline then fails to import the
# module with "SyntaxError: Invalid or unexpected token" — see today's
# investigation. The other .mjs test in the repo
# (tests/scripts/ai-review-core.test.ts → scripts/lib/ai-review-core.mjs)
# does not have this problem because that file has no shebang.
#
# Cross-platform safe rule: any file that runs as a script (shebang at
# top) must use LF universally. Listing both .mjs (Node ESM scripts) and
# .sh (bash) covers the executable surface in this repo.

*.mjs text eol=lf
*.sh  text eol=lf
